{
  "doc_id": "22758",
  "text": "Rosids comprise the largest clade among eudicots (20 orders and 140 families), and include plants that form nitrogen-fixing symbioses (Elaeagnaceae, Rhamnaceae, Rosaceae, and Ulmaceae) [CITATION_1] , as well as many important crops (Fabaceae (legumne) and Rosaceae (fruit crops)). Accordingly, rosids plants have been very well studied, and almost the entire chloroplast genome is known [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
